  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Establishing penalties for non-compliance\n- Creating investigative frameworks\n\n4. Financial Institution Obligations\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Maintaining comprehensive records\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Jurisdictional Considerations\n- Varying international legal standards\n- Cross-border cooperation\n- Extradition agreements\n\n7. Technological Adaptations\n- Regulations covering digital currencies\n- Cyber-transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced digital forensic capabilities\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes systematically.",
